commit.message:
DOC: First pass at format conversion, rst -> myst (#4863)

* First commit for myst
 * Add myst-parser to doc requirements
 * Add myst-parser extension to conf.py
 * Start working on the overview doc.

* Convert overview to myst syntax

* Convert api_changes to myst.

 * Switch to #-based headings to suppress markdown parse warnings
 * ignore inconsistencies between emph/literal - assume all are
   intended to be inline literals

* mystify install.

 * Leave link to INSTALL.rst using include directive.

* mystify user guide stub page.

 * Illustrate the toctree directive in myst syntax.

* glossary directive and inline role syntax

* mystify contribute.

 * NOTE: Left CONTRIBUTING.TXT alone even though it has rst
   syntax as it might be used elsewhere.

* mystify license stub

* mystify core dev article

* mystify skips stub

* mystify values

* mystify CoC

* Get rid of lingering sphinx warnings

* Fix some broken links caught by CI

* Revert "mystify contribute."

This reverts commit 46c61ee57559e5c5b4d8d64948709ca12bee1d84.

* Revert "mystify install."

This reverts commit 3fa567c and updates include directives accordingly

Co-authored-by: Emmanuelle Gouillart <emmanuelle.gouillart@nsup.org>

commit.message:
Fix benchmarks so they can be run on older scikit-image commits (#4891)

* add missing multichannel=False argument to segmentation.slic benchmarks

add start_label=1 to avoid FutureWarning

* reduce size of image in slic benchmarks

avoids timeout when running "asv dev"

* add versionadded label for start_label argument of slic

* only start_label kwarg only exists in skimage>=0.17.0

add test cases with multichannel=True

* guard against non-existant metrics module in benchmarks

metrics was not present in older skimage versions

guard against failed import of registration module

registration module was introduced in 0.16

guard against import of binary blobs for older skimage

guard against import of denoise_nl_means in older versions

make benchmark_transform_warp imports compatible with older versions

* add versionadded comment to mask argument of slic

* fix misnamed variable

* provide default multichannel argument to avoid warnings on older skimage

* restore original asv.conf.json values

* fix sixe of self.msk in slic benchmarks

* reviewer comments

make sure registration & metrics tests are listed as n/a rather than failed in older skimage

* fix typo return->raise

* remove invalid multichannel argument [ci skip][skip ci]

* skip multiotsu tests for older skimage

* skip skeletonize3d tests for older skimage

* deal with move and rename of feature.registrater_translation

* split masked slic tests into a derived class

this way can mark these cases as n/a on older skimage

* split 3d Sobel to a separate class (unavailable in older scikit-image)

[ci skip][skip ci]

* use a version-dependent skeletonization function

* refer to new function name in PhaseCrossCorrelationRegistration

* fix spelling of Restoration

commit.message:
just remove normalization factor altogether for efficiency

Both _compute_error and _compute_phasediff are invariant to the absolute scale
It is only important that CCmax, src_amp and target_amp are scaled consistently with each other.
fix bug in normalization factor calcuation (assumed ndim=2)
use real(a*a.conj()) to calculate np.abs(a)**2 efficiently
simplify error calculation in phase_cross_correlation
